      "blurb": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p>Hardlight is the common name for the substance that forms holograms. As modern cultures learned to bend light and plasma into substantial shapes, their efforts caused living hardlight beings to emerge into reality. Most living hardlight creatures must remain near the projector that gives them life, but a few have found ways to exist without their projectors. Hardlight scamps are among the least of these beings.</p><p>Beginning as hardlight sparks, these creatures often reshape themselves to vaguely resemble the ad or media they were born from, though they often also resemble bat-like elemental scamps, thus earning their name. Most hardlight scamps, like true scamps, are mischievous and annoying in their efforts to advertise, but the ad they were born from also influences their behavior. A hardlight scamp advertising plushies might be more playful than one advertising a cybernetic augmentation for photosynthetic skin.</p><h2>Living Hardlight</h2><p>Hardlight scamps are just one type of living hardlight that might be encountered in the Universe. Hardlight sparks are short-lived but lively manifestations that fade as quickly as they burn to life or evolve into more substantial beings like hardlight scamps. Living holograms form from artificial intelligences that gain souls, and though they need a projector to interact with the world, they have their own hopes and dreams like any other sapient being. In the right conditions, hardlight can take even stranger and more powerful shapes.</p>",
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Starfinder Second Edition Playtest Adventure: A Cosmic Birthday",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "ORC",
        "remaster": true
      }
